title: Made in Minnesota: Flavors only found in the Twin Cities
text:
Last Slide Next Slide 
We tend to think of New York City, San Francisco, even New Orleans when it comes to dining destinations. But the Twin Cities — Minneapolis and St. Paul, Minn. — are becoming hot spots for culinary creativity right this moment. The area is crawling with talent and it seems that you can’t throw a rock here without finding a James Beard Award winner. From megastar chef Gavin Kaysen, who left his NYC gig to reclaim roots in Minneapolis, to ultra-fine French dining to a kooky “country club on crack,” here’s a guide to food and drink experiences that can only be found in the Twin Cities.
